{ This is the most tenacious. After the immediate   11...cxb4  12.Nb5 !  +-  is even stronger. White's knight will hop to c7 ot d6 with devastating effect.  Closing the queenside with   11...c4  isn't better. Black survives tactically but without counterplay on the queenside his position is just bad.  12.Qh3  Now Black's queen is in trouble.  Qc6   12...b5  13.axb6  Qxb6  14.b5  +-  13.b5  Qc8  14.f4  g6  15.Ba3  +- }
2. cxd3 cxb4 { 12...cxd4  13.Nb5  +-  is very similar. } 3. Nb5
{ White will win material. The computer shows the very weird } 3... Nb8
{ as the most tenacious. } 4. Nc7+ Kd7 5. Nxa8
{ Black will pick up the knight on a8 and have some compensation for the missing exchange. White is clearly for choice though. }
