1. Qb5 { preparing a queen shift to the kingside. } 1... Bb7
{ Other moves that save the c6 knight are refuted in the same manner like the mainline.   14...Na5  15.Bxh7+ !  Kxh7  16.Qh5+  Kg8  17.Ng5  +-   14...Bd7  15.Bxh7+ !  +-   14...Ne7  15.Bxh7+ !  +- }
2. Bxh7+ Kxh7 { 15...Kh8  16.Qh5  +- } 3. Qh5+ Kg8 4. Ng5 Re8 5. Qxf7+
{ followed by the typical mating mechanism   18...Kh8  19.Qh5+  Kg8  20.Qh7+  Kf8  21.Qh8+  Ke7  22.Qxg7#   18.Qh7+ ?  Kf8  19.Qh8+  Ke7  20.Qxg7  Kd7 !  ∓  and Black is out of the woods. }
*

