3. Ng5 { 14.Qxc6  Be6  +=  isn't much } 3... g6 4. Qxc6 Qe7
{ Now   15...Be6  can simply be answered by  16.Nxe6  +- } 5. Qxd5
{ 16.Qxa8 ?!  Bb7  17.Qxa7  Ra8  isn't clear even if White is objectively better after  18.Qxa8+  Bxa8  19.Bf3  ± }
5... Qxe2 6. Be3 Bf5 { 17...Rb8  18.Qe5  Bb7  19.Nxf7  +- } 7. Nxf7
{ The damaged king position guarantees a quick win for White, e.g.   18...Rae8  19.Nh6+  Kg7  20.Qd4+  Rf6  21.Bg5  +- }
*

