{ 19.Nxg7 ?!  Kxg7  20.Rxe6   20.Bxh6+ ?  Kxh6  21.Qd2+  Kh7  22.Ng5+  Kg8  -+  20...Qc8  21.Bxh6+  Kxh6  22.Qe3+  Kg7  23.h6+  Kh7  24.Rxe7  Rxe7  25.Qxe7  Rf8  +=  gives White an advantage, but is not as good as the mainline. }
1... fxe6 2. Nxg7
{ 20.Nxh6+  gxh6  21.Bxh6  Bf8  22.Qg6+  Kh8  23.Bxf8  Rxf8  24.Ng5  Rde8  25.Qh6+  Kg8  26.Qg6+  Kh8 =  only leads to a perpetual. }
2... Kxg7 3. Bxh6+ Kh8 4. Bg7+ { 22.Qg6 ??  Rg8  -+ } 4... Kxg7 5. Qg6+ Kh8 6.
Ng5
{ as after   24...Rf8  25.h6  Black can't prevent both Qg7# and Nf7# at the same time. }
